description: The secrets of the Grey Witch revealed! We finally find out a little more about the mysterious Grey Witch and her past. And while she plots her next move, Deedlit, Ghim, and Slayn plan theirs. Their travels are interrupted, though, when they encounter a knight from the Holy Order of Valis... the order to which Parns father had belonged!

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: All-ages manga! Despite the advice of Slayn, Ghim rushes off after the Grey Witch, convinced she is really Leylia, the daughter of Neese, the girl he has been searching for. Concerned about his well-being, Deedlit rushes off after him. They stumble upon a fallen war party and learn that Princess Fianna of Valis has been kidnapped. United again, the group picks up the kidnappers trail and come upon a house where the bandits seem to be resting. But unbeknownst to our heroes, the bandits are ready for them! Let the battle begin!

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Our heroes learn that the Holy Knights of Valis are chasing a carriage that carries a kidnapped princess. With the knights hot in pursuit of the carriage, the group is suddenly blinded by a bright flash and thrown by a deafening boom. Using enhanced vision spells, Slayn and Deedlit are able to see that the party has been attacked by the Grey Witch. They rush to the aid of the Knights, but will they be able to reach them in time to save them?

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Karla has identified the weaknesses of all our heroes and used these faults to finally capture them. With all threats to her plans now at bay, Karla puts the final motions in action in her quest to rule Lodoss. As Parn, Deedlit, and Ghim plot to escape, Karla raises an army of undead skeletons. Will they and the others be able to free themselves in time to try and stop Karla's newest evil machinations?

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Our heroes learn that it is indeed Princess Fianna that has been kidnapped and they refuse to allow Karla to use her as a pawn. As they steal away with her into the night, they head for Valis, hoping they are in time to stop the war from escalating. However, Karla is not going to let her prize slip through her fingers so easily and chases after Deedlit, Parn and company herself. If you want something done right, do it yourself, and Karla is going to put an end to their meddling once and for all!

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Just when you thought it was safe to go back on the road! Its the final showdown! Sick to death of their meddling, Karla goes after Deedlit, Parn, Ghim, Slayn, Etoh and Woodchuck herself. Taking the shape of a giant black bird, she descends on the group as they head for Valis. It's do or die and the six noble warriors are in for the fight of their lives against evil incarnate.

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: As the troops fight to drive back the evil forces of Marmo and the Grey Witch, Parn is told the truth about his father. Believing him worthy of finally knowing the truth, an old friend and confidant of Parn's dad at long last explains to Parn exactly what happened to his father. How will this new information affect Parn and will he have the chance to honor his father's memory?

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: After learning the truth about his father, Tessius, Parn is anxious to rush into battle and prove he can live up to the standards set by the heroic acts of his father. Meanwhile, the Holy Knights plot a strategy to defend Lodoss from the onslaught of evil. Realizing that the forces of Marmo, enhanced by evil magic, are too powerful for a direct assault, they plan on the side of caution. They also try to convince the remaining neutral lands of Lodoss to join their cause and protect what is rightfully theirs.

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Having rescued the Princess of Valis from her kidnappers, including the Grey Witch; Deedlit, Parn, and the rest of the adventuring band accompany her to her home, the capital city of Roid. There, she is reunited with her father, the King of Valis, in his magnificent throne room. Their emotional reunion gives way to dark thoughts as the king realizes the dark forces arrayed against them and the power of Karla, the Grey Witch.

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: The knights of Flaim arrive at the Kingdom of Valis. King Fahn presents Parn with a sword, not only as a reward for rescuing the princess of Valis from her kidnappers, but also in honor of his father Sir Tessius, who was wrongly disgraced at his death. Parn later volunteers to lead an expedition through the abandoned cave of the dwarves, now inhabited by a dragon and man-eating ogres. Parn seeks the great sage Wort, whose power will be needed in the battle against Marmo and the Grey Witch.

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: Parn volunteers to lead a dangerous expedition through the abandoned cave of the dwarves, now inhabited by a dragon and man-eating ogres, to find the great sage Wort, whose power will be needed in the battle against Marmo and the Grey Witch. When he, Deedlit, and the others enter the great tower where Wort lives, they are met with a surprise... Wort is not alone... and his companion is none other than Karla, the Grey Witch! What does this mean for Lodoss; has Wort allied himself with the Grey Witch, or is there a deeper game afoot?!

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch

description: In this issue, the mystery of Wort's apparent alliance with the Grey Witch is revealed. Is he the only force holding the forces of evil at bay through mysterious manipulation of history and warfare on Lodoss? After their confrontation with Wort, Parn, Deedlit the Elf, and the others return to Valis where they are called to attend the council of war. And, in the final act of redemption in the drama of his wrongly disgraced father, Parn is presented with his new garb... the armor of the order of the Knights of Tessius! Adventure, magic, and mystery from the pen of Ryo Mizunu, with more superb art by Yoshihiko Ochi!

volume.name: Record of Lodoss War: The Grey Witch
